  "body": "## HOW TO REPRODUCE\n\n```\n$ ruby -v\nruby 2.0.0p648 (2015-12-16 revision 53162) [x86_64-darwin15.2.0]\n$ gem install fluentd\n$ touch foo.conf\n$ fluentd -c foo.conf\n2016-05-24 21:45:55 +0900 [info]: reading config file path=\"foo.conf\"\n2016-05-24 21:45:55 +0900 [info]: starting fluentd-0.12.24\n/Users/seo.naotoshi/.rbenv/versions/2.0.0-p648/lib/ruby/2.0.0/rubygems/core_ext/kernel_require.rb:55:in `require': cannot load such file -- string-scrub (LoadError)\n        from /Users/seo.naotoshi/.rbenv/versions/2.0.0-p648/lib/ruby/2.0.0/rubygems/core_ext/kernel_require.rb:55:in `require'\n```\n## CAUSE\n\nWith this PR https://github.com/fluent/fluentd/pull/937, string-scrub was removed from runtime-dependency. See https://rubygems.org/gems/fluentd/versions/0.12.24.\n\nThis change\n\n```\n  unless \"\".respond_to?(:scrub)\n    gem.add_runtime_dependency(\"string-scrub\", [\">= 0.1.1\"])\n  end\n```\n\nmeans that do `gem.add_runtime_dependency` if ruby < 2.1 (which does not have scrub methods) on **release** timing, not on `gem install`. Because fluentd v0.12.24 was released with ruby >= 2.1 (I guess so, only repeatedly knows), the dependency was removed. \n",
